        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 2 at 4:29PM CDT until June 2 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 20 miles east of
Saragosa, or 26 miles west of Fort Stockton, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Firestone Test Track.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 228 and 254.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
